### Test API Key Authentication

@hostname = https://localhost:7142

### Test public endpoint (no auth required)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/public

### Test endpoint that accepts all auth schemes - Using API Key (Admin)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/all
X-API-Key: dev-api-key-12345

### Test endpoint that accepts all auth schemes - Using API Key (User)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/all
X-API-Key: prod-api-key-67890

### Test endpoint that accepts all auth schemes - Using API Key (Read-Only)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/all
X-API-Key: readonly-api-key-11111

### Test API Key-only endpoint with Admin Key
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/apikey
X-API-Key: dev-api-key-12345

### Test API Key-only endpoint with User Key
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/apikey
X-API-Key: prod-api-key-67890

### Test API Key-only endpoint with Read-Only Key
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/apikey
X-API-Key: readonly-api-key-11111

### Test JWT or API Key endpoint with API Key
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/jwt-or-apikey
X-API-Key: dev-api-key-12345

### Test JWT-only endpoint with API Key (should fail)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/jwt
X-API-Key: dev-api-key-12345

### Test with expired API Key (should fail)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/apikey
X-API-Key: expired-api-key-99999

### Test with invalid API Key (should fail)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/apikey
X-API-Key: invalid-api-key

### Test without API Key header (should fail)
GET {{hostname}}/api/secure/apikey

### WeatherForecast with API Key Authentication
GET {{hostname}}/weatherforecast
X-API-Key: dev-api-key-12345

###
# Available API Keys for testing:
# 
# 1. dev-api-key-12345 (Admin)
#    Owner: admin (ID: 1)
#    Scopes: read, write, admin
#    Roles: Administrator
#    Status: Active, expires in 1 year
#
# 2. prod-api-key-67890 (User)
